freetext.SYSTEMIC_REACTION_OTHER: Blood glucose level continues to spike both on waking as well as during the day. Taking longer period for those levels to go below 130 in spite of my no changes being made to my dietary intake. Felt more tired today than yesterday.
Continued disrupted sleep and weird dreams.

I develooped a cold sore starting on the 4th day and continuing. I get these once in a while and this time it was nit just on my lip but also on the side of the bulb of my nose. It is still active and spread a little more on my lip. It is mild but it is there.

Insomnia, higher blood glucose levels on waking, blood sugar levels staying higher than my baseline which is usually between 110-119 due to my strict dietary intake -I have Type 2 diabetes. Lack of appetite too.
Intermittent sleep with 4 hours at a time but could go back to sleep right away. Weird dreams..
Lack of appetite, hypersomnia fir 38 hours-slept from 6:00 pm on Feb 15th-till 8:00 am this morning.
Sprained neck. Sneezing from Jan 24th to 26th but no other symptoms of cold such as runny  nose. Also had slight cough during that same period.

Still sleeping 12-15 hours for 6 nights in a row. First spell was 38 hours at a stretch with 10-15 minute waking used for eating blueberries or pistachio nuts and falling right back asleep. 4 mornings of weird dreams.
